Oct 18 2009 	Le Nouvel Hotel - Montreal Quebec Canada	Great hotel. Even though our room faced the busy street on the front of the hotel, we never heard noises. The room was very well kept. Nice furnishings, though they could've had an ottoman for the chair. Free wireless internet service accessible from the room. Bathroom was sparse, but functional. Great cable tv -- many channels to choose from, if you liked (though Montreal being such a great city, why you would spend much time in front of the tv is a mystery to me). The hotel includes a full 'American breakfast' in its price. Very good food, even if it was the same thing day in and out. At least you could fuel up for the day's adventure ahead and not need to worry about where to get breakfast. Excellent service at the front desk. If you need a refrig in your room, ask and it shall be delivered promptly. Same thing goes for bathrobes! It is a centrally located hotel, and well worth the modest room rates. Excellent value! We would most certainly stay there again. 	
